Faf du Plessis on Monday confirmed that he was stepping down from his remaining Proteas captaincy gigs in order to concentrate on contributing as a senior batsman. Poignantly, the 35-year-old stalwart noted that “the last season of my captaincy has been the most challenging to date as I had a lot of off-field issues that I devoted my energy towards”. Indeed, Du Plessis had to navigate his way through the dramatic fallout from a disastrous World Cup, which not only affected the national team’s performance, but also led to a corporate governance meltdown at Cricket South Africa. It’s quite easy...